<h3 class="ds-h3">How to consume an icon in Figma</h3>

<ol class="ds-ol">
  <li class="ds-li">Open your project file within Figma</li>
  <li class="ds-li">Navigate to the Assets panel in the left sidebar</li>
  <li class="ds-li">Enable the <a href="https://www.figma.com/file/TLnoT5AYQfy3tZ0H68BgOr/Flight-Icons?node-id=164%3A0" rel="external">Flight Icons</a> Library </li>
  <li class="ds-li">Click the Team library icon (looks like an open book), toggle on Flight Icons</li>
  <li class="ds-li">Search or scroll to find the icon you want to use and drag it into your file</li>
</ol>

<div class="ds-info">
  <p class="ds-p">üí° Tip: Swapping instances, sizes, and colors is easy to do from the right sidebar</p>
</div>

<h3 class="ds-h3">Best Practices</h3>

<h4 class="ds-h4">Icon Types</h4>

<p class="ds-p">
  <img alt="example of icon types" src="assets/images/icon-types.png" width="900" class="ds-img" />

  <ul class="ds-ul">
    <li class="ds-li">Use the `Generic` style icons by default</li>
    <li class="ds-li">Use the `Filled` style if indicating the toggled state of an icon</li>
    <li class="ds-li">Use the `Filled` style where contrast against other icons is important</li>
    <li class="ds-li">Use the `Off` style icons to indicate a disabled state</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h4 class="ds-h4">Icon Sizes</h4>
<p class="ds-p">
  <img alt="example of icon sizes" src="/assets/images/icon-sizes.png" width="900" class="ds-img" />

  <ul class="ds-ul">
    <li class="ds-li">Use the `16px` size in product interfaces</li>
    <li class="ds-li">Use the `24px` size in marketing pages</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h5 class="ds-h5">Guidance</h5>
<p class="ds-p">
  <ul class="ds-ul">
    <li class="ds-li">‚úÖ Display icons at either `16px` or `24px` </li>
    <li class="ds-li">‚úÖ Use `16px` icons by default in product interfaces  </li>
    <li class="ds-li">‚úÖ Consider using `24px` icons in product interfaces for empty states  </li>
    <li class="ds-li">‚ö†Ô∏è Take care if choosing to display icons at sizes other than `16px` and `24px`  </li>
    <li class="ds-li"> <i>There may be cases where 16px and 24px values don't fit a design - Flight icons can be resized in these cases but be aware that the design is not optimized for values other than these.</i></li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h5 class="ds-h5">Updating existing interfaces</h5>

<ul class="ds-ul">
  <li class="ds-li">‚úÖ Where the current icon size is less than or equal to `20px`, replace icons with `16px` versions </li>
  <li class="ds-li">‚úÖ If the size of icon to be replaced is at least `21px`, first try to replace it with a `24px` version </li>
  <li class="ds-li"><i>If 24px seems too large, consider dropping down to 16px and reworking the interface for a better fit</i></li>
</ul>

